cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on image captioning, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel auto-encoder framework, which involves learning a shared dictionary between the textual and visual domains, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the MS-COCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark for multimedia research, and thus could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
